What problem does it solve?
- we want to make something with just ideas in our head, but there's just too much boilerplate we need to go through

Gatsby will let you
- just focus on your code and logic
- forget front/back boilerplates
- easily host your site on netlify

How is Gatsby doing that?
- it uses React and GraphQL under the hood

CMS(Content management system) is dying
- they are moving to headless CMS
- future of web development is the "content mash"

What is Gatsby?
- it's a PWA generator